summary: An Ordinance submitting to the qualified voters of the City of Seattle at the general election to be held in said City Tuesday, March 2, 1915, the proposition of the issuance and sale by sale City of its general bonds in the sum of Eight Hundred Twenty-nine Thousand, Five Hundred ($829,500.) Dollars, for the purpose of providing money for the construction of a bridge for the City of Seattle across the Lake Washington Canal and of a bridge across Salmon By Waterway.
